OL,6,FThe Infected Blood Inquiry warned
OL,7,Fthere has been a "repetition of the
OL,8,Fmistakes of the past" said the number
OL,9,Fof people who have been compensated to
OL,10,Fdate is "profoundly unsatisfactory",
OL,11,Fcalling for "faster and fairer"
OL,12,Fcompensation for victims.
OL,14,FSir Brian provided nine
OL,15,Frecommendations in total, including a
OL,16,Fproposal that victims should be able
OL,17,Fto apply for compensation, rather than
OL,18,Fhave to be invited.
