OL,3,CInfected blood victims 'harmed
OL,4,Cfurther' by compensation scheme delays
OL,6,FMore than 30,000 people in the UK were
OL,7,Finfected with HIV and hepatitis C
OL,8,Fafter they were given contaminated
OL,9,Fblood and blood products between the
OL,10,F1970s and early 1990s.
OL,12,FMore than 3,000 people have died as a
OL,13,Fresult, while survivors are living
OL,14,Fwith lifelong health implications.
OL,16,FThe Infected Blood Inquiry heard
OL,17,Fevidence over four years from hundreds
OL,18,Fof witnesses.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
