OL,6,FSince the Infected Blood Inquiry was
OL,7,Fannounced in July 2017, it is
OL,8,Festimated that 710 infected and
OL,9,Faffected people died by the time the
OL,10,Ffinal report was published in May 2024.
OL,12,FThe Inquiry's final report said the
OL,13,Fscandal "could largely have been
OL,14,Favoided" and there was a "pervasive"
OL,15,Fcover-up to hide the truth.
OL,17,FBoth government and health officials
OL,18,Fwere accused of "deception", including
OL,19,Fdestroying documents to "save face and
OL,20,Fsave expense".
