OL,6,FSome #11.8 billion has been allocated
OL,7,Fto compensate victims, organised
OL,8,Fthrough the IBCA.
OL,10,FAs of July 1, 2,043 people have been
OL,11,Finvited to make a claim, according to
OL,12,FIBCA figures, and 460 people have had
OL,13,Ftheir compensation paid, totalling
OL,14,Fmore than #326 million.
OL,16,FA lawyer representing victims of the
OL,17,Fscandal said victims and their
OL,18,Ffamilies are still in the dark about
OL,19,Fwhen they can expect to receive
OL,20,Fcompensation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/17
